Is it just me...<br>
___________________________<br>
<br>
That's the understatement of the year. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   Nobody seems happy.  There have been a lot of posts about magician DPS compared to other classes and I understand that in a grouping/raid situation.  As a soloist, the biggest thing I could get would be some kind of a root/quick escape spell which I doubt will ever happen.   <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ualladdim.showPublicProfile?language=EN>alladdim</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 18<br> <font color=#333333>(10/16/02 11:34 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1587.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_sunglasses.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: New Spells</span><hr size=1> Actually, I used to think how other class are out nuking us and out healing us, etc etc. But now that I stopped and look at our class from a 3rd person perspective I realize how powerful and needed our mage class is. We can summon focus items, haste items, ultravision necklace, armor for our pets, resist items, mod rods, and soon gate necklace as well as proccing weapons (that can be used by pets). And our most important spell: Call of the Hero. Can any other class do that? It's all unique to our mage class and its something none may take away. <p><p align="center"><a
href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=150542"
target="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=150542"><img
