width="595" height="164"></a></p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ubaisblackfingers.showPublicProfile?language=EN>BaisBlackfingers</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 49<br> <font color=#333333>(10/16/02 11:53 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1587.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_sunglasses.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: New Spells</span><hr size=1> Aye alla, I hear that.  We really do rock everyone's world, I think maybe necros have an advantage (past the person behind the keys who makes all the difference) on us in duels just 'cuz they can fear our pet and we can't fear theirs.<br>
<br>
And we are a great class to have in a group.  So great in fact that people are often shocked.  I think that's the real problem-mages get no love =(<br>
<br>
Ought we be doing more?  I think so.  I started my mage back when people still thought it was funny to take a druid as a nuker over a mage.  Back (ever so long ago) when rogues would actually listen to mages and learn to time backstabs on air-pet stuns.  Rogues used to be smart enough to make a mage-rogue group viable- even kickass.<br>
<br>
But it's more important for people to <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> know</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--> that mages rule.  I haven't been asked for a coldstone in 20some levels, and only get asked for focus as toys (granted I don't have the full final circle of focus items yet).<br>
<br>
The other thing is that the things we are needed for are taken for granted.  Nobody dies because the mod-rod didn't come through in time for the heal.  They die because the cleric didn't heal fast enough.  Even though it may be the mod-rod's fault.  People notice a good cleric when the heal comes in just right.  People don't notice a good mage who balances rodding just right to keep the cleric up but still saves the day with a nicely timed nuke.  No mage lovin.<br>
<br>
That and the proccing weapons.  I got SoR a couple of days before the (n-word deleted to keep the flames down) and have always wanted it back.  But that's just a personal thing.  Objectively proccing weapons aren't <!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><i> needed</i><!--EZCODE ITALIC END-->.  Just highly, highly (for me) desired.  Like druids desire heals.  I'm done now. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/utangting.showPublicProfile?language=EN>TangTing</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 85<br> <font color=#333333>(10/17/02 1:39 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1587.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_sunglasses.gif" align=absmiddle>  Proccing weapons</span><hr size=1> It would have been nice to get the proccing weapons at a lower level - I remember lvl 38 still using those lvl 34 pets was brutal. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uliffthemage.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Liff the Mage</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Magician</span><br>  Posts: 32<br> <font color=#333333>(10/21/02 12:33 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerspells.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1587.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Not just you</span><hr size=1> __ <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerspells.showPrevMessage?topicID=1587.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub102.ezboard.